Sr. Data Scientist		KSM Consulting		Indianapolis, IN, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>Job Description<br /><br /><strong>Summary Of Responsibilities<br /><br /></strong>Apply advanced mathematics and predictive analytics to solve some of our client&apos;s most challenging problems.  Work with a team to implement practical solutions that turn our findings into real results.<br /><br /><strong>Essential Functions<br /></strong><ul><li>Apply and develop machine learning and other advanced analytics algorithms</li><li>Collaborate with software developers to plan and construct the architecture of model deployment</li><li>Maintain a working knowledge of data mining and visualization best practices</li><li>Architect backend development of advanced analytics and software solutions</li><li>Work closely with the data analytics practice director and other practice directors, solution architects, product manager, and project managers on requirements, solution architecture, and development execution.</li><li>Involvement in client-facing project activities such as requirements gathering, solution reviews, and explaining technical complexities and business benefits in layperson terms.</li><li>Helping define the data analytics solution delivery methodology.</li><li>R&amp;D and long-term positioning of the data analytics practice around current and emerging technologies.<br /><br /></li></ul><strong>Qualifications<br /><br /></strong>Skills and Experience:<br /> <br /><ul><li>2+ years experience in data science or data analytics</li><li>Experience developing algorithms with Python and/or R is required</li><li>Strong ETL and data cleanup skills required</li><li>Experience with distributed computing highly desirable</li><li>Strong working knowledge of modern data mining and machine learning methods</li><li>Strong statistics, mathematics, computer science, numerical methods, and data visualization</li><li>Strong background in linear algebra and probability required</li><li>Experience with data analysis on a variety of database platforms required, particularly NoSQL</li><li>Experience with Bayesian analysis highly desirable</li><li>Regular expression and text mining skills highly desirable</li><li>Rapid prototyping and development skills required</li><li>Development experience on Linux/Mac required</li><li>Strong solution creativity and effective written, verbal, and presentation skills</li><li>Entrepreneurial inclination to discover novel opportunities for applying analytical techniques to business and social problems</li><li>Collaborative team player who is detailed oriented, focused on solution quality and execution</li><li>Comfortable working across wide range of project sizes and industries<br /><br /></li></ul><strong>Education<br /><br /></strong>Bachelor’s Degree required<br /><br /><strong>Working Conditions<br /><br /></strong>Occasional travel to client locations.  <br /><br />Additional Information<br /><br />All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, color, sex, disability, national origin, race, religion, or veteran status. <br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">KSM Consulting is a technology, data analytics, and management consulting firm. <br /><br />KSMC helps clients maximize their technological and operational excellence to better achieve their goals. While some of clients come to us for short term project needs, or for urgent “turnaround" operations, we strive to build long-term relationships that grow in value through perspective, foresight, consistency, and the continuous refinement of our clients’ key systems and structures.<br /><br />Serving two distinct markets – the public sector and private businesses – we understand that every client and situation is wholly unique, and we treat each accordingly. The KSMC team brings seasoned technical guidance along with the confidence and flexibility to guide organizations from their current state to the realization of their objectives.<br /><br />Over 70 employees and rapidly growing, KSM Consulting is part of the employee-owned Katz, Sapper &amp; Miller Network headquartered in Indianapolis, Indiana.<br /><br />In 2015, KSM Consulting was honored as a TechPoint Mira Award nominee, the Microsoft Central Region Rising Star of the Year Award winner, and the GovTech Horizon Award in Administration winner.</div>